<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 6:54PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN PITTSYLVANIA AND
SOUTHWESTERN HALIFAX COUNTIES THROUGH 730 PM EDT...
At 654 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Milton, or 7 miles west of Turbeville, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
South Boston...
Turbeville...
Ingram...
Milton...
and Elmo.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
